Cameroon’s Trade Deficit Widened Last Year, Ministry Says

-- B y   P i u s   L u k o n g
-- 
2011-09-07T11:17:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-07/cameroon-s-trade-deficit-widened-last-year-ministry-says-1-.html
Cameroon’s trade deficit widened to
619 billion  CFA francs  ($1.3 billion) in 2010 from 419 billion
francs the previous year, the Ministry of Finance said.  Exports increased 15 percent to 1,912 billion francs and
imports rose 21 percent to 2,531 billion francs, according to a
ministry statement handed to reporters yesterday in the West
African nation’s capital, Yaounde. Crude oil was the biggest
export item, accounting for 37 percent of the total.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pius Lukong in Yaounde at 
 plukong@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net . 